Definition: characterized by a firm and humorless belief in the validity of your opinions
Example: both sides were deeply in earnest, even passionate; an entirely sincere and cruel tyrant; a film with a solemn social message
Synonyms: noun, attribute, earnestness, sincere, feeling, sincerity, solemn, solemnity, characterized, by, a, firm, and, humorless, belief, in, the, validity, of, your, opinions, both, sides, were, deeply, even, passionate, an, entirely, cruel, tyrant, film, with, social, message
Category: adj.all
